# Git workflow (CV Studio)

## Permission

- **Do not commit or push** without explicit user permission.
- Before committing, give a short summary of what changed.

## Pre-commit

Run **`pnpm run check`** (or at least `pnpm run lint` + `pnpm run typecheck` + `pnpm format` if you only need a lighter pass).

## Commits

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/): `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`.

Examples: `feat(editor): add repo URL field`, `fix(print): margin clipping`.

## Branches

`feature/<kebab-case>`, `fix/<kebab-case>`, `docs/<kebab-case>`. Branch from `main` unless the user says otherwise.

## Pull requests

Open or update PRs **only when the user asks**. If opening one, ensure **`pnpm run check`** passes locally first.
